This paper deals with topology control and network lifetime in wireless sensor networks, which are typically studied in the computer science sub-category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also involves the partitioning of a 3D space into cells, which can be considered as a form of distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The paper also involves optimization of network lifetime, which can be considered as a form of systems and control (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT).
